    {
      "_key": "faqs",
      "_type": "faqSection",
      "backgroundImage": null,
      "faqs": [
        {
          "_key": "faq1",
          "_type": "faq",
          "answer": "Wear fitted, comfortable workout attire that allows for plenty of skin contact—such as shorts with a sports bra or tank—to ensure a secure grip on the pole. DO NOT apply lotions or oils before class; they make the pole slippery and can endanger anyone using it. Remember to bring your water bottle!",
          "question": "What should I wear to class?"
        },
        {
          "_key": "faq2",
          "_type": "faq",
          "answer": "Pole shoes can be worn in all classes, but going barefoot is often more comfortable when learning new tricks. For Exotic Baddies and Heels & Queens, heels and knee pads are recommended—though beginners are always welcome to dance barefoot. For Heels & Queens, any comfortable heels are fine if you don't have pole shoes yet. Please bring a water bottle and a small towel; pole grip and a yoga mat, if you have them. Absolute beginners only need water and a towel to get started!",
          "question": "What should I bring with me to class?"
        },
        {
          "_key": "faq3",
          "_type": "faq",
          "answer": "Your first class will focus on learning the basics in a supportive, judgment-free environment. You can expect a guided warm-up, an introduction to foundational moves, and time to practice at your own pace. No experience is required—just come ready to move, learn, and have fun.",
          "question": "What should I expect in my first session?"
        },
        {
          "_key": "faq4",
          "_type": "faq",
          "answer": "We require cancellations to be made at least 24 hours before class to avoid losing your credit. Late cancellations or no-shows are non-refundable, as they prevent others from taking your spot. We do not offer cash refunds, but are happy to reschedule with advance notice.",
          "question": "What's your cancellation policy?"
        },
        {
          "_key": "faq5",
          "_type": "faq",
          "answer": "No! We are beginner-friendly and are excited to welcome you to the studio and introduce you to this athletic artform we adore. We hope you love it as much as we do!",
          "question": "Do I need any prior experience?"
        },
        {
          "_key": "faq6",
          "_type": "faq",
          "answer": "Yes! Free street parking is available, and there is additional paid garage parking nearby for your convenience. We recommend arriving a few minutes early to allow time to park and settle in.",
          "question": "Is there parking available?"
        }
      ],
